OL,6,FAfter the verdicts were delivered,
OL,7,Ffamily members hugged their legal
OL,8,Frepresentatives. Others wiped away
OL,9,Ftears. One member of the jury became
OL,10,Fvisibly emotional.JThe coroner thanked
OL,11,Fthe jury for their service, stating
OL,12,Fthat "the passing of years hasn't
OL,13,Fdiminished the horror of some of the
OL,14,Fevidence that you have heard".JAt that
OL,15,Fpoint, families of the victims stood
OL,16,Fup in unison and applauded the jury
OL,17,Fmembers at length, with one person
OL,18,Fshouting "thank you".
