OL,6,F"Forty-eight young people never came
OL,7,Fhome that night, but as Taoiseach I
OL,8,Fwant to say this to their families;
OL,9,FYou never gave up on justice for them,
OL,10,Fyou never let Ireland forget about
OL,11,Fthem. They were never alone, and our
OL,12,Fcountry owes you a great debt for
OL,13,Fthat."
